The paper focuses on developing an intelligent software system that integrates machine learning with user interaction to improve code completion in HTML editors. This involves building decision trees using the ID3 algorithm and displaying them in an interactive rules interface system (IRIS) for developers to modify or delete. The paper also discusses the results of a user study that validates the effectiveness of the user interaction in enhancing autocomplete accuracy and developer productivity. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of machine learning algorithms and user interaction also suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as possible sub-categories.
